  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684230202544-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684230202544-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684230202544-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684230202544-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684230202544-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, add the <strong>peanut butter</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!), <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the juice of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> to a small bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir until fully combined – this is your <strong>satay sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684230207702-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684230207702-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684230207702-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684230207702-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684230207702-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>finely</p><p>Slice the<strong> cucumber</strong> finely</p><p>Chop the<strong> coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684230212459-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684230212459-x400.jpg",
